Sentencas: Solid oxide fuel cell (SCFC) running directly on hydrocarbon fuels has attracted much attention in recent years.
Titulo: Characterization of the Ni-ScSZ anode with a LSCM-CeO2 catalyst layer in thin film solid oxide fuel cell running on ethanol fuel

Sentencas: In this paper, a dual-layer Structure anode running on ethanol is fabricated by tape casting and screen-printing method, the addition of a LSCM-CeO2 catalyst layer to the supported anode surface yields better performance in ethanol fuel.
Titulo: Characterization of the Ni-ScSZ anode with a LSCM-CeO2 catalyst layer in thin film solid oxide fuel cell running on ethanol fuel

Sentencas: The effect that the synthesis conditions of the catalyst layer have on the performances of the composite anodes is investigated.
Titulo: Characterization of the Ni-ScSZ anode with a LSCM-CeO2 catalyst layer in thin film solid oxide fuel cell running on ethanol fuel

Sentencas: Single cells with this anode are also fabricated, of which the maximum power density reaches 669mW cm(-2) at 850 degrees C running on ethanol steam.
Titulo: Characterization of the Ni-ScSZ anode with a LSCM-CeO2 catalyst layer in thin film solid oxide fuel cell running on ethanol fuel

Sentencas: No significant degradation in performance has been observed after 216 h of cell testing when the Ni-ScSZ13 anode is exposed to ethanol steam at 700 degrees C. Very little carbon is detected on the anode, suggesting that carbon deposition is limited during cell operation.
Titulo: Characterization of the Ni-ScSZ anode with a LSCM-CeO2 catalyst layer in thin film solid oxide fuel cell running on ethanol fuel

Sentencas: Consequently, the LSCM-CeO2 catalyst layer on the surface of the supported anode makes it possible to have good stability for long-term operation in ethanol fuel due to low carbon deposition.
Titulo: Characterization of the Ni-ScSZ anode with a LSCM-CeO2 catalyst layer in thin film solid oxide fuel cell running on ethanol fuel
